# libraries
library(tidyverse)
library(vegan)

# data
# bird communities
birds <- read_csv(here::here("data","bird-comm.csv")) %>% 
  column_to_rownames("site")

# environmental variables
env <- read_csv(here::here("data","env-var.csv"))

# set up a "metadata" frame - will be useful for plotting later!
site_type <- env %>% 
  # selects the named columns
  select(site, landtype)

How speciose are my communities?

# vegan::specnumber() counts the number of species in each site
# output is a named vector
sppr <- specnumber(birds)

# stats::aov fits nalysis of variance statistical model: are group means different?
sppr_aov <- aov(sppr ~ landtype, data = site_type)
summary(sppr_aov)
##              Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value Pr(>F)  
## landtype      2     86    43.0   2.774 0.0648 .
## Residuals   207   3209    15.5                 
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
# creates a dataframe from specnumber() output for plotting
sppr_df <- sppr %>% 
  # converts a named vector into a dataframe
  enframe() %>% 
  # join with site_type dataframe for easier plotting
  full_join(site_type, by = c("name" = "site"))

sppr_plot <- ggplot(sppr_df, aes(x = landtype, y = value, color = landtype)) +
  geom_boxplot()
sppr_plot

How diverse are my communities?

# vegan::diversity() calculates diversity indices
shannondiv <- diversity(birds)

# try simpson's diversity
simpsondiv <- diversity(birds, index = "simpson")
shandiv_df <- shannondiv %>% 
  # putting the named vector into a dataframe
  enframe() %>% 
  # joining the dataframe with metadata
  full_join(., site_type, by = c("name" = "site")) %>% 
  # calculating mean shannon diversity for each landtype
  group_by(landtype) %>% 
  summarize(mean = mean(value))

shandiv_plot <- ggplot(shandiv_df, aes(x = landtype, y = mean, fill = landtype)) +
  geom_col()
shandiv_plot

How different are my communities in species composition?

# str(pcabiplot) in console

# extract coordinates etc. from biplot
PCAscores <- as.data.frame(pcabiplot$sites) %>% 
  bind_cols(site_type, .)

PCAvect <- as.data.frame(pcabiplot$species)

# plot in ggplot
PCA_plot <- ggplot(PCAscores) +

# vegan::cca() correspondence analysis
# only shows variation in community structure that is related to the variables
# only choosing environmental variables that you're interested in
# CCA will perform logistic regression on the distance object
birdCCA <- cca(birds ~ canopy_height + stems_ha + big_stem_bas, data = env)

  geom_point(aes(x = CCA1, y = CCA2, color = landtype), shape = 19) +

  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(-10, 16)) +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(-3, 12)) +
  geom_point(data = species_data, aes(x = CCA1, y = CCA2), shape = 17, size = 2, color = "blue") +
  geom_text(data = ccavectors, aes(x = CCA1, y = CCA2, label = rownames(ccavectors)))
